<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Crowdsourcing credibility</title>
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>

    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Merriweather&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">
    <!-- Compiled and minified JavaScript -->
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>
  </head>

  <body>
    <nav class="bar noselect">

    <span>
      <button class="btn" data-custom-open="instruction" role="button">Instruction</button>
      
      <% if !@direction.nil? %>
        <b> &nbsp; <%= @direction.html_safe %></b>
      <% end %>
    </span>

    </nav>
    <div class="wrapper">
      <%= yield %>
    </div>


  <div class="modal micromodal-slide" id="instruction" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal__overlay" tabindex="-1" data-micromodal-close>
      <div class="modal__container" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="modal-1-title">
        <header class="modal__header">
          <h2 class="modal__title" id="modal-1-title">
              Instruction
          </h2>

          <button class="modal__close" aria-label="Close modal" data-micromodal-close></button>
        </header>

        <main class="modal__content" id="modal-1-content">
          <p>
              There are 3 sections in this task, and it will take approximately 30 minutes in total.<br>
              You cannot go back to previous section, once you leave it.
          </p>
          <br>
          <p>
              <strong>Section 1. Pre-experiment Survey</strong><br>
              In this section, you <strong>must</strong> answer <strong>all</strong> survey questions.
          </p>
          <br>
          <p>
              <strong>Section 2. Logical Fallacy Judgement</strong><br>
              In this section, you will learn the concept of false dilemma with representative examples.<br>
              After then, you will read 44 tweets from politicians and judge whether each tweet has false dilemma or not.
          </p>
          <br>
          <p>
              <strong>Section 3. Post-experiment Survey</strong><br>
              In this section, you should complete a questionnaire based on your experience in Section 2.
          </p>
          <br>


        <!--
            <p>
                <strong>Section 3. Survey</strong><br>
                In this section, you <strong>must</strong> answer <strong>all</strong> survey questions.<br>
                There is a question that you can get correct only if you read the article in section 2, so <strong>make sure you read it</strong>.<br>
                <strong>If you get it wrong, you will get <span class="red">disadvantage</span></strong>. <br><br>

            </p>
        -->

            <p>
                After you finish all sections above, you will be shown a page with <span class="red">finish token</span>.<br>
                Please submit this token back in mTurk task page.<br><br>
                You can always decide not to participate in the experiment and can withdraw your participation anytime.<br>
                Even if you refuse to participate in this research, you will not be disadvantaged at all.<br><br>
                If you have any questions or wish to express any discomfort related to this research, please feel free to contact the researcher below.<br>
                <strong>Name of researcher: Donghoon Han, Contact: hoonhan.d@kaist.ac.kr</strong>
            </p>
        </main>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  </body>

  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/1.0.0/js/materialize.min.js"></script>

</html>
